Detailed Description

cvmx_ase_backdoor_rsp_ctl

This register is used to indicate that the backdoor response is complete. See description in ASE_BACKDOOR_REQ_CTL. Hardware asserts [VALID] when the full response packet has been received and has been posted to [CNT] and ASE_BACKDOOR_RSP_DATA(). Hardware does not change [CNT] and ASE_BACKDOOR_RSP_DATA() while [VALID] is asserted. Hardware deasserts [VALID] when ASE_BACKDOOR_REQ_CTL[VALID] is triggered.
